n in an accessible style that will appeal to both scholars and devotees of Toews’s work, Lives Lived, Lives Imagined is a timely examination of Toews’s oeuvre and a celebration of fiction’s ability to simultaneously embody compassion and anger, joy and sadness, and to brave the personal and communal oppressions of politics, religion, family, society, and mental illness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh  aAutofiction.  aCanadian literature.  aDisability Studies.  aMennonite.  aMiriam Toews.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177284011740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772840117423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772840117/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles